            <h1>Mortgage News</h1>
            <p>In todays Mortgage Rate world the benchmark 30-year fixed mortgage rate is 2.940% with an APR of 3.230%. The average 15-year fixed mortgage rate is 2.390% with an APR of 2.720%. The 5/1 adjustable-rate mortgage (ARM) rate is 2.940% with an APR of 4.000%, according to Bankrate’s latest survey of the nation’s largest mortgage lenders. </p>
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.nerdwallet.com/mortgages/mortgage-rates">View Todays Rates for Your Area!</a>
            <p>The average rate on the 30-year fixed-rate mortgage started sliding by mid-March and never stopped dropping. Average rates have stayed below 3% since July 30, according to Freddie Mac's Primary Mortgage Market Survey. But these sub-3% rates likely won't last in 2021, according to most experts.</p>
            <a target="_blank" href="https://www.google.com/url?sa=t&rct=j&q=&esrc=s&source=web&cd=&cad=rja&uact=8&ved=2ahUKEwjXwaum3vLuAhVSGs0KHY5oCJUQFjAFegQIBxAD&url=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fadvisor%2Fmortgages%2Fmortgage-interest-rates-forecast%2F&usg=AOvVaw2zY-o4ZJYCGa_iCxs_I9xr">View Todays Trends in Mortgage Rates</a>
            <p>Plenty of homeowners are refinancing now. Lenders are enduring heavy workloads. You can do your part to lighten the load by submitting a complete application, with all the necessary documentation. Online applications usually will let you know if you haven’t provided all the necessary documents.</p>
